Facets

One plot converted into many plots using facet_wrap() or facet_grid()

bins / binning

cut_iterval(x, n) - divides data into n bins, each bin same width. cut_width(x, width) - divides data into n bins, each bin of width wide. cut_number(x, n) - divides data into n n bins.

Aesthetics

ggplot(pets) + 
  aes(age, weight, colour = sex) + 
  geom_point() + 
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = c(1, 6, 10), 
                     labels = c("1" = "Baby",
                                "6" = "Grown up",
                                "10" = "Over the hill")) + 
  scale_y_continuous(breaks = c(6,8,10),
                     labels = c("6" = "Small",
                                "8" = "Medium",
                                "10" = "Large"))

ggplot(flatPrices) + 
  aes(x = Date, y = AvgFlatPrice) + 
  geom_line() + 
  ylab("average flat price \n") + 
  scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::dollar_format(prefix = ""))

flatPrices <- flatPrices %>%
  mutate(percent_change = AvgFlatPrice/AvgFlatPrice[1])

ggplot(flatPrices) + 
  aes(x = Date, y = percent_change) + 
  geom_line() + 
  scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::percent) + 
  ylab("percent change relative to start \n")

Changing limit of scales.

ggplot(pets, aes(age, weight)) +
  geom_point(aes(colour = sex), size = 4) +
  scale_x_continuous(
    name = "Age",
    breaks = seq(13),
    limits = c(1,8)
  ) + 
  scale_y_continuous(
    name = "Weight",
    breaks = c(6, 8, 10),
    labels = c(
      "6" = "Light",
      "8" = "Normal",
      "10" = "Heavy"
    ), 
    limits = c(1,8)
  )

ggplot(whisky) + 
  aes(x = YearFound, y = Capacity, color = Region) + 
  geom_point() +
  #scale_x_reverse()
  scale_y_continuous(trans = "log10")

ggplot(whisky) + 
  aes(x = YearFound, fill = Region) + 
  geom_histogram(bins = 30) +
  #coord_flip()
  coord_fixed()

PieCharts

snacks <- data.frame(
  group = c("Cakes", "Biscuits", "Jaffa Cakes"),
  count = c(30, 50, 20)
)
ggplot(snacks) + 
  aes(x = " ", y = count, fill = group) +
  geom_bar(width = 0.5, stat = "identity") + 
  xlab("biscuits") + 
  # to make a pie chart : 
  coord_polar("y")
